abstract: Death toll from recent passenger boat sinking rises to 63 as rescuers recover 40 more bodies from Gulf of Bone in central Indonesia; disaster mitigation agency revises number of survivors to 40, saying one person had been counted twice; fifteen people are still missing.
lead_paragraph: Rescuers on Thursday recovered 40 bodies from waters in central Indonesia, raising the confirmed death toll from the weekend sinking of a passenger boat to 63.

headline.print_headline: Asia; Indonesia: Boat Disaster’s Toll Rises
